---
description: Visual QA host-safety and chrome-devtools isolation procedure
alwaysApply: true
---

The terms MUST, MUST NOT, SHOULD, SHOULD NOT, and MAY use RFC 2119 meanings.

When browser inspection or Visual QA applies, agents MUST use the `chrome-devtools`
MCP server. Open a fresh, dedicated page with `new_page` in a unique isolated
context (for example via the server's `--isolated` flag). You MUST NOT attach to
an operator's personal browser or use the personal `com.google.Chrome` identity for
MCP automation.

You MUST close every page you open with `close_page` when verification finishes,
including on failure. Record `isolatedContext` confirmation and every `close_page`
action in case evidence.

You MUST NOT change macOS Launch Services, the default browser, or Chrome
preferences as remediation. You MUST NOT kill or quit all MCP Chrome processes as
the primary remediation.

Prefer Chrome for Testing with `chrome-devtools-mcp` `--executablePath` and
`--isolated` hardening when operators configure MCP locally. Use Playwright MCP
only as an explicit fallback when chrome-devtools is unavailable.
